main event: A UFO sighting was reported by military personnel at Glasgow AFB, Montana on 24 February 1967, involving at least two objects that were bright, white, and round.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be much larger than a star and at an estimated altitude of 30,000 feet,One object was observed for a few minutes, while a second object was observed for about one hour by multiple witnesses,The first object showed up on radar but had intermittent activity and was difficult to track,Conflicting reports suggested the presence of flashing lights and sound similar to an engine were heard by one witness,Analysis concluded that the available data was insufficient for a conclusive evaluation of the sightings.
witness description: military personnel including Sergeants Vaughn, Hansen, and others
